.PP
protocol\&.nntp\&.header_entries \fB<str>\fR (default: "Subject,From,Date,Message\-ID,Newsgroups")
.RS 4
Comma separated list of which entries in the article header to show\&. E\&.g\&. \*(AqSubject\*(Aq and \*(AqFrom\*(Aq\&. All header entries can be read in the header info dialog\&.
.RE
.SS "protocol\&.rewrite (URI rewriting)"
.sp
Rules for rewriting URIs entered in the goto dialog\&. It makes it possible to define a set of prefixes that will be expanded if they match a string entered in the goto dialog\&. The prefixes can be dumb, meaning that they work only like URI abbreviations, or smart ones, making it possible to pass arguments to them like search engine keywords\&.
.PP
protocol\&.rewrite\&.default_template \fB<str>\fR (default: "")
.RS 4
Default URI template used when the string entered in the goto dialog does not appear to be a URI or a filename (i\&.e\&. contains no \*(Aq\&.\*(Aq, \*(Aq:\*(Aq or \*(Aq/\*(Aq characters), and does not match any defined prefixes\&. Set the value to "" to disable use of the default template rewrite rule\&.
.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}
%c in the template means the current URL,
.RE
